# Scoreboard ‚Äî Project Architecture

## Purpose

Beach tennis scoreboard application. Tracks points, games, sets and matches in real time following official beach tennis rules.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend framework | React 19 |
| Backend framework | NestJS 11 |
| Auth | Keycloak 26.5.6 (custom Docker image ‚Äî `apps/auth/`) |
| Language | TypeScript 5.9 |
| Frontend build | Vite 8 |
| Mobile app | Expo SDK 54 ¬∑ React Native 0.81 (`apps/mobile`, `@scoreboard/mobile`) |
| Backend build | NestJS CLI (webpack) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS 4 (`@tailwindcss/vite` plugin) |
| Routing | TanStack Router (code-based, `apps/frontend/src/router.tsx`) |
| Server state / HTTP cache | TanStack Query (`@tanstack/react-query`) ‚Äî queries/mutations against the Nest API |
| HTTP client (backend) | axios (`apps/frontend/src/api/`) ‚Äî base URL from `env.VITE_API_URL`, Bearer from `useAuth().token` |
| Client-side persistence | RxDB 16 + Dexie 4 (IndexedDB ‚Äî matches, players offline / local cache) |
| API database | PostgreSQL + Prisma 7 (`apps/backend`) ‚Äî migrations, `PrismaService`, generated client under `src/generated/prisma/` |
| Testing | Vitest 4 (frontend/core) ¬∑ Jest 30 (backend) |
| Package manager | pnpm workspaces |
| Monorepo | Turborepo |
| CI/CD | GitHub Actions + release-it + Conventional Commits |

## Monorepo Structure

