### Environment variables (Joi validation)

All frontend env vars are validated at startup via `infrastructure/env.ts`. The app **crashes immediately** if a required variable is missing. Variables must be prefixed with `VITE_` (Vite convention). See `.env.example` for the template.

| Variable | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `VITE_KEYCLOAK_URL` | **yes** | Keycloak base URL |
| `VITE_KEYCLOAK_REALM` | **yes** | Keycloak realm name |
| `VITE_KEYCLOAK_CLIENT` | **yes** | Keycloak client ID |
| `VITE_API_URL` | **yes** | Base URL of the NestJS API (no trailing slash; e.g. `http://localhost:3000`). Inlined at build time; pass `VITE_API_URL` as a Docker `--build-arg` when building `apps/frontend/Dockerfile`. |

### Authentication (Keycloak)

Uses `keycloak-js` directly (no `@react-keycloak/web`). The `AuthProvider` wraps the entire app with `onLoad: 'login-required'` ‚Äî no route renders before authentication. Token refresh uses three layers: proactive interval (60s), `onTokenExpired` callback, and `visibilitychange` listener. Use `useAuth()` hook to access user info, roles, **`token` (Bearer for API calls)**, and logout.

### Backend HTTP (NestJS)

- **`src/api/`** ‚Äî axios instance with `baseURL` from `env.VITE_API_URL`; each request adds `Authorization: Bearer <Keycloak access token>`.
- **`src/queries/`** ‚Äî TanStack Query hooks (e.g. `usePlayerMe` ‚Üí `GET /players/me`). Prefer `enabled: Boolean(token)` so queries do not run without a token.
- **Providers** ‚Äî `main.tsx`: `QueryClientProvider` wraps `RouterProvider` and sits inside `AuthProvider` so hooks can read `useAuth().token`.
- **API validation** ‚Äî the Nest app (`apps/backend`) validates the same Bearer tokens using `nest-keycloak-connect` (`KeycloakConnectModule` + global guards). Env vars `KEYCLOAK_*` are validated with Joi at startup (see `.cursor/rules/backend.mdc`).

**Persistence split:** the **browser** uses RxDB/IndexedDB under `infrastructure/persistence/` for offline-capable match/player documents. The **Nest API** uses **PostgreSQL + Prisma** for authoritative player (and future) relational data. They are separate: REST + TanStack Query sync with the server; RxDB remains optional local storage.

## App: `apps/backend` (`@scoreboard/backend`)

NestJS 11 REST API. Imports `@scoreboard/core` via workspace dependency for access to the domain and application layer.

```
apps/backend/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prisma/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ schema.prisma      ‚Üê PostgreSQL models (e.g. Player), enums
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ migrations/        ‚Üê `prisma migrate` history (committed)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prisma.config.ts       ‚Üê Prisma 7 project config
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ src/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app.module.ts          ‚Üê Root NestJS module
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app.controller.ts      ‚Üê Root controller
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app.service.ts         ‚Üê Root service
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ auth/                  ‚Üê Keycloak: AuthModule, KeycloakConfigModule, KeycloakConfigService
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config/                ‚Üê app, database, auth (+ Joi validation.schema)
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prisma/                ‚Üê PrismaModule + PrismaService
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ generated/prisma/      ‚Üê Generated client (from `prisma generate`)
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ players/               ‚Üê Example feature module
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ main.ts                ‚Üê Bootstrap ‚Äî `enableShutdownHooks()` for Prisma disconnect
```

- `paths` in `tsconfig.json` resolve `@scoreboard/core/*` ‚Üí `../../packages/core/src/*` for both type-checking and webpack build.
- `moduleNameMapper` in Jest config mirrors the same resolution for tests.
- Dockerfile at `apps/backend/Dockerfile` builds a minimal production image using `turbo prune`, copies `prisma/` into the runtime image, and runs **`prisma migrate deploy`** before `node dist/main.js` (see `backend.mdc`).

## App: `apps/auth` (`@scoreboard/auth`)

Custom Keycloak 26.5.6 Docker image with passwordless Email OTP authentication ‚Äî **not a Node.js/TypeScript app**, not part of the pnpm workspace or Turborepo pipeline.

```
apps/auth/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Dockerfile              ‚Üê Production image (postgres, health, metrics, --optimized)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Dockerfile.local        ‚Üê Development image (start-dev mode)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ VERSION                 ‚Üê Plain-text version (used by CI for git tags / GitHub Releases)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ themes/                 ‚Üê FreeMarker login/account/email themes (future)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ providers/              ‚Üê Java SPI JARs (future custom providers)
```

- Both `docker-compose.yml` (dev) and `docker-compose.prod.yml` build from `apps/auth/Dockerfile*`.
- **Bundled provider:** [keycloak-magic-link](https://github.com/p2-inc/keycloak-magic-link) v0.59 ‚Äî downloaded from Maven Central via `ADD` in the Dockerfile. Provides Email OTP authenticator with auto-registration (`forceCreate`).
- **Email delivery:** Resend SMTP (`smtp.resend.com:587` + StartTLS). Configured per Realm in the Keycloak Admin Console.
- Future Java providers will be compiled with Maven and the resulting JARs copied into the image at build time.
- Versioned via `VERSION` file + git tags (`@scoreboard/auth@X.Y.Z`) + GitHub Releases ‚Äî no release-it.

## CI/CD

GitHub Actions + release-it + Conventional Commits. Full details in `cicd.mdc`.

- `ci.yml` ‚Äî commitlint + check-types + test + build (triggers on PRs)
- `release.yml` ‚Äî CI + per-package release with path-based change detection (triggers on push to `main`)
- Commits follow `type(scope): description` ‚Äî scopes: `core`, `frontend`, `backend`, `mobile`, `auth`, `shared`, `ci`, `deps`, `release`

## Key Architectural Decisions

1. **`@scoreboard/core` is framework-agnostic** ‚Äî no React, no Vite, no Tailwind inside `packages/core/src/`.
2. **Aggregate root (`Match`) is the only public mutation surface** ‚Äî call `match.start()` and `match.scorePoint()`. Never mutate inner entities directly.
3. **Domain events** are collected via `match.pullDomainEvents()` after each mutation and dispatched by the application layer.
4. **No parameter properties** in constructors ‚Äî `erasableSyntaxOnly: true` in tsconfig. Use the Props pattern instead.
5. **Factory methods** (`Entity.create()`, `Entity.restore()`) replace `new Entity(...)` calls from outside the class.
6. **Tests live in `__tests__/`** folders at the same level as the file they test, inside `packages/core/src/`.
7. **Commits follow Conventional Commits** ‚Äî use scoped commits (`feat(core):`, `fix(frontend):`, `feat(backend):`, `feat(mobile):`, `feat(auth):`) to trigger releases only for the affected package. See `cicd.mdc` for full details.
8. **Backend uses `paths` for core resolution** ‚Äî `@scoreboard/core/*` is mapped to `../../packages/core/src/*` in `apps/backend/tsconfig.json`. This allows webpack and ts-node to resolve TypeScript source files without a compiled `dist/`. Jest uses the equivalent `moduleNameMapper`.
9. **Environment variables are validated at startup** ‚Äî both backend (`@nestjs/config` + Joi) and frontend (`infrastructure/env.ts` + Joi) crash immediately with descriptive errors if required env vars are missing or invalid. Never read `import.meta.env` or `process.env` directly ‚Äî import from the validated `env` module instead.
10. **Frontend auth uses `keycloak-js` directly** ‚Äî no wrapper library. `AuthProvider` wraps the entire app with `onLoad: 'login-required'`. Use the `useAuth()` hook to access user info, roles, and logout.
11. **Frontend ‚Üî Nest API** ‚Äî Use `env.VITE_API_URL` (never raw `import.meta.env`); axios in `src/api/` for transport; TanStack Query in `src/queries/` for server cache; send `Authorization: Bearer` with `useAuth().token` on every backend request. The backend validates tokens with Keycloak (`nest-keycloak-connect`); configure `KEYCLOAK_*` env vars (see `backend.mdc`).
12. **Where data lives** ‚Äî Frontend: IndexedDB via RxDB. Backend API: PostgreSQL via Prisma; schema and migrations live in `apps/backend/prisma/`; production containers apply migrations at startup (`migrate deploy`).
13. **Mobile** ‚Äî `@scoreboard/mobile` (Expo) lives under `apps/mobile`; participates in Turborepo (`pnpm build` exports web to `dist/`); native builds use **EAS**; releases use **release-it** with tags `@scoreboard/mobile@X.Y.Z` (see `cicd.mdc`).
